g2:c.FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT: This is a regression test for GENSYMCID-588 ' 'Inconsistencies in G2 connection function 'items-are-connected (item-1, items-2)'' There are 169 separated test cases summarized in the table. Notes. 1. We didnt' verify that tests execute correctly in current version. Instead, we blindly assumed that current operation of G2 at some random point in HIP2016-08 is correct. This is not good generally, but approved by PA and SEM. The test will fail if the behavior changes in the future. 2. To refresh expected test results to be equal to current results, first of all use "fill in results table" on the subworkspace of benchmark test. Then edit colors of EXPECTED-RESULTS to match those of RESULTS. If you're lazy to do that manually, copy the table-cells of results to your favorite text editor and replace regexp in cells which refer to items-are-connected with something innocent, e.g., "@"-@"". I used "ted (.+)" in Lispworks editor to start with. Assign new value to the table-cells of expected-results and all colors would change automagically.
Tests for items-are-connected. See release notes on sub-sub-workspaces of benchmark-tests

g2:c.FUNCTION-DEFINITION.g2:a.TEXT: is-cp-source (CP) = there exists a object OBJ connected at the input of CP such that (items-are-connected (OBJ, CP))
